Package au.csiro.pathling.terminology

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    TerminologyFunctions
    Describes the interface to the terminology functions from a library context.
    TerminologyOperation<ResponseType,​ResultType>
    An abstraction of a terminology operation that describes how to validate, execute and extract a result from the response.
    TerminologyParameters
    Represents parameters that are passed to a terminology operation.
    TerminologyService
    Abstraction layer for the terminology related operations.
    TerminologyService.PropertyOrDesignation
    Common interface for properties and designations
    TerminologyServiceFactory
    Represents something that creates a TerminologyService.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    BaseTerminologyService
    Common functionality for all implementations of TerminologyService.
    DefaultTerminologyService
    The default implementation of the TerminologyServiceFactory accessing the REST interface of FHIR compliant terminology server.
    DefaultTerminologyServiceFactory
    Default implementation of TerminologyServiceFactory, providing the appropriate implementation of TerminologyService based upon the given configuration.
    RequestRetryHandler
    Overrides the default retry handler to add logging.
    TerminologyResult<ResultType extends Serializable>
    Represents the result of a terminology operation, along with metadata that can be used for caching.
    TerminologyService.Designation
    The representation of a designation of a concept.
    TerminologyService.Property
    The representation of the property of a concept.
    TerminologyService.Translation
    Represent a single translation of a code.
  • Exception Summary 
    Exception Description
    ResponseNotModifiedError
